<br>
Did bandwidth go up?  No<br>
<br>
Did they hire more staff?  No<br>
<br>
Server prices &amp; Bandwidth has gone down.  All computer equipment has gone way down since EQ was first released.  The only thing that has gone up is paying thier staff.  <br>
<br>
Overall I think thier costs have gone down, not up. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/urexron.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rexron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Pie Guy </span><br>  Posts: 830<br> <font color=#333333>(3/26/02 1:35:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1069.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.orderofhasson.com/members/khamhorse.jpg HEIGHT=160 WIDTH=102 ></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pardon my French, but What the fuck?!</span><hr size=1> However, ROI on any startup business in the techonology field is usually 2-3 years.  I think I once mentioned I used to work for Sony, and that's how 90% of the projects we did were budgeted (I worked for a segment of their Semiconductor business, which they sold because, after 4 years, their return wasnt what they planned).  Who's to say Sony's made any money on EQ yet?  No idea the costs they had to encounter to get the game off the ground, including new buildings, wiring, servers, office equipement, staff, etc.<br>
<br>
Listen, I'm not defending them.  I haven't seen their P&L's and the people I know that used to work in Sony's audit staff are long gone :)  But to think they made money "out of the gate" and are thus getting a 14 mill revenue increase is a bit off the mark.  Dont forget Uncle Sam walks away with 5.4 million of that in taxes (assuming 39%).<br>
<br>
Dont think they arent paying people.  They may not pay guides, but dont full GM's get paid?  And their customer service people?  And their programmers (suckers drain companies)?  And their utilities.  I mean God, I run a mid sized printing plant and our electricity bill is $105,000 a month.  I'm willing to bet Sony's is atleast double that.  Probably more due to having to cool the places where the equipement is.<br>
<br>
I've got 2 accounts, and i'm more than willing to pay the extra $3.00 per account per month.  Will I pay more than that, no.  I wont go passed $15.00 a month, ever.  I will cancel my accounts the day it becomes $15.01.  But there arent that many places that you can get as much fun and enjoyment and use out of $13.00 a month as you do EQ.  Try giving the dude at Gameworks $15.00 and say "Give me a fourty hour card please".<br>
<br>
